msgstr "Zu Ihrem TS hinzufügen:"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:221
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { parse } from \"my-bindings\";\n"
"const buf = await Bun.file(\"input.pdf\").bytes();\n"
"console.log(parse(buf));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { parse } from \"my-bindings\";\n"
"const buf = await Bun.file(\"input.pdf\").bytes();\n"
"console.log(parse(buf));\n"
"```"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:227
msgid "Then `perry compile main.ts -o main && ./main`."
msgstr "Dann `perry compile main.ts -o main && ./main`."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:229
msgid "5. Publish"
msgstr "5. Veröffentlichen"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:231
msgid "Tag a release"
msgstr "Ein Release taggen"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:238
msgid ""
"The scaffolded `.github/workflows/release.yml` builds prebuilt staticlibs "
"for x86_64 + aarch64 macOS/Linux + Windows on tag and attaches them to the "
"GitHub release. Add or remove targets in the workflow's `matrix` block as "
"needed."
msgstr ""
"Das gerüstete `.github/workflows/release.yml` baut bei Tags vorgebaute "
"Staticlibs für x86_64 + aarch64 macOS/Linux + Windows und hängt sie an das "
"GitHub-Release an. Fügen Sie nach Bedarf Targets im `matrix`-Block des "
"Workflows hinzu oder entfernen sie."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:243
msgid "npm publish"
msgstr "npm publish"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:249
msgid ""
"The scaffolded `package.json` includes the right `files: [...]` list to "
"bundle `src/` + `Cargo.toml` + the README. If you also vendor the prebuilt "
"artifacts in the npm tarball, add them to the `files` block."
msgstr ""
"Die gerüstete `package.json` enthält die richtige `files: [...]`-Liste, um "
"`src/` + `Cargo.toml` + die README zu bündeln. Wenn Sie die vorgebauten "
"Artefakte auch im npm-Tarball mitliefern, fügen Sie sie dem `files`-Block "
"hinzu."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:253
msgid "Two distribution models"
msgstr "Zwei Distributionsmodelle"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:255
msgid "There are two ways your users get the staticlib:"
msgstr "Es gibt zwei Wege, wie Ihre Nutzer die staticlib bekommen:"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:257
msgid "Model"
msgstr "Modell"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:257
msgid "What ships in the npm tarball"
msgstr "Was im npm-Tarball mitgeliefert wird"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:257
msgid "Trade-off"
msgstr "Trade-off"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:259
msgid "**Vendor prebuilts**"
msgstr "**Vendor-Prebuilds**"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:259
msgid ""
"`src/`, `Cargo.toml`, AND `prebuilt/<target>/lib<name>.a` for every target"
msgstr ""
"`src/`, `Cargo.toml` UND `prebuilt/<target>/lib<name>.a` für jedes Target"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:259
msgid ""
"Bigger npm tarball; install is fast (no compile); user doesn't need a Rust "
"toolchain"
msgstr ""
"Größerer npm-Tarball; Installation ist schnell (kein Kompilieren); Nutzer "
"braucht keine Rust-Toolchain"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:260
msgid "**Source-only**"
msgstr "**Nur Quellcode**"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:260
msgid "`src/`, `Cargo.toml`, no prebuilts"
msgstr "`src/`, `Cargo.toml`, keine Prebuilds"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:260
msgid ""
"Tiny tarball; first `perry compile` runs `cargo build --release` (slow); "
"user needs Rust"
msgstr ""
"Winziger Tarball; das erste `perry compile` führt `cargo build --release` "
"aus (langsam); Nutzer braucht Rust"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:262
msgid ""
"Vendoring is the friendlier default for npm consumers. Source-only makes "
"sense if your matrix is too big for one tarball or if you're publishing a "
"private wrapper to a small audience."
msgstr ""
"Vendoring ist die freundlichere Standardeinstellung für npm-Konsumenten. "
"Nur-Quellcode macht Sinn, wenn Ihre Matrix zu groß für einen Tarball ist "
"oder wenn Sie einen privaten Wrapper an ein kleines Publikum "
"veröffentlichen."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:266
msgid ""
"The manifest's `targets.<target>.prebuilt` field tells Perry where to find a"
" prebuilt for the user's compile target:"
msgstr ""
"Das `targets.<target>.prebuilt`-Feld des Manifests teilt Perry mit, wo ein "
"Prebuild für das Compile-Target des Nutzers zu finden ist:"

