"// targets: ios-simulator, web, wasm\n"
"\n"
"import { App, VStack, Text, TextArea, State } from \"perry/ui\"\n"
"\n"
"const content = State(\"\")\n"
"\n"
"App({\n"
"    title: \"TextArea\",\n"
"    width: 500,\n"
"    height: 400,\n"
"    body: VStack(12, [\n"
"        TextArea(\"Enter multi-line text...\", (value: string) => content.set(value)),\n"
"        Text(`Length: ${content.value.length}`),\n"
"    ]),\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:315
msgid "**Helpers:** `textareaSetString`."
msgstr "**Helfer:** `textareaSetString`."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:317 src/cli/perry-toml.md:108
msgid "Sections"
msgstr "Abschnitte"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:319
msgid ""
"Group controls into labelled sections. Perry has no `Form()` widget — use a "
"`VStack` of `Section(title)`s and attach children via `widgetAddChild`."
msgstr ""
"Gruppieren Sie Steuerelemente in beschriftete Abschnitte. Perry hat kein "
"`Form()`-Widget — verwenden Sie ein `VStack` von `Section(title)`s und "
"hängen Sie Kinder über `widgetAddChild` an."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:322
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"// demonstrates: Section grouping with widgetAddChild (no Form widget in Perry)\n"
"// docs: docs/src/ui/widgets.md\n"
"// platforms: macos, linux, windows\n"
"// targets: ios-simulator, web, wasm\n"
"\n"
"import {\n"
"    App,\n"
"    VStack,\n"
"    Section,\n"
"    TextField,\n"
"    Toggle,\n"
"    State,\n"
"    widgetAddChild,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\"\n"
"\n"
"const name = State(\"\")\n"
"const notifications = State(true)\n"
"\n"
"const personal = Section(\"Personal Info\")\n"
"widgetAddChild(personal, TextField(\"Name\", (value: string) => name.set(value)))\n"
"\n"
"const settings = Section(\"Settings\")\n"
"widgetAddChild(\n"
"    settings,\n"
"    Toggle(\"Notifications\", (on: boolean) => notifications.set(on)),\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"App({\n"
"    title: \"Sections\",\n"
"    width: 500,\n"
"    height: 400,\n"
"    body: VStack(16, [personal, settings]),\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:358
msgid "Mobile widgets (issue #553)"
msgstr "Mobile-Widgets (Issue #553)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:360
msgid "BottomNavigation"
msgstr "BottomNavigation"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:362
msgid ""
"5-tab bottom bar with icon + label + badge per tab. `onSelect(index)` fires "
"when the user taps; `bottomNavSetSelected` is the programmatic counterpart "
"and does NOT fire `onSelect`."
msgstr ""
"5-Tab-Bottom-Bar mit Icon + Label + Badge pro Tab. `onSelect(index)` löst "
"aus, wenn der Nutzer tippt; `bottomNavSetSelected` ist das programmatische "
"Gegenstück und löst `onSelect` NICHT aus."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:366
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  BottomNavigation,\n"
"  bottomNavAddItem,\n"
"  bottomNavSetBadge,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const bar = BottomNavigation((index) => {\n"
"  console.log(\"tab:\", index);\n"
"});\n"
"bottomNavAddItem(bar, \"house\", \"Home\");\n"
"bottomNavAddItem(bar, \"magnifyingglass\", \"Search\");\n"
"bottomNavAddItem(bar, \"bell\", \"Activity\");\n"
"bottomNavSetBadge(bar, 2, \"5\");\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:382
msgid ""
"Real on macOS (`NSStackView` + `NSButton` strip with SF Symbol icons), iOS "
"(`UITabBar`), Android (custom `LinearLayout` strip with badge overlay), and "
"GTK4 (`GtkBox` + Adwaita CSS). Stub on Windows, tvOS, visionOS, watchOS."
msgstr ""
"Echt auf macOS (`NSStackView` + `NSButton`-Strip mit SF-Symbol-Icons), iOS "
"(`UITabBar`), Android (benutzerdefinierter `LinearLayout`-Strip mit Badge-"
"Overlay) und GTK4 (`GtkBox` + Adwaita-CSS). Stub auf Windows, tvOS, "
"visionOS, watchOS."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:387
msgid "ImageGallery"
msgstr "ImageGallery"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:389
msgid ""
"Swipeable, paging carousel of images. Local file paths load synchronously; "
"HTTP/HTTPS URLs are fetched on a background queue and applied on the main "
"thread."
msgstr ""
"Wischbares, seitenweise blätterndes Karussell von Bildern. Lokale Dateipfade"
" laden synchron; HTTP/HTTPS-URLs werden auf einer Hintergrund-Queue geladen "
"und auf dem Main-Thread angewendet."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:393
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { ImageGallery, imageGalleryAddImage } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const gallery = ImageGallery((idx) => console.log(\"page:\", idx));\n"
"imageGalleryAddImage(gallery, \"/photos/01.jpg\", \"Hero shot\");\n"
"imageGalleryAddImage(gallery, \"https://cdn.example/photo2.jpg\", \"Wide angle\");\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:401
msgid ""
"Real on macOS (`NSScrollView` paging), iOS (`UIScrollView` with "
"`scrollViewDidEndDecelerating`), Android (`HorizontalScrollView`), GTK4 "
"(`GtkScrolledWindow` + `GtkPicture`). Stub on Windows, tvOS, visionOS, "
"watchOS."
msgstr ""
"Echt auf macOS (`NSScrollView`-Paging), iOS (`UIScrollView` mit "
"`scrollViewDidEndDecelerating`), Android (`HorizontalScrollView`), GTK4 "
"(`GtkScrolledWindow` + `GtkPicture`). Stub auf Windows, tvOS, visionOS, "
"watchOS."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:406
msgid "Pull-to-refresh"
msgstr "Pull-to-refresh"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:408
msgid ""
"Available on `ScrollView` and `LazyVStack`. The `onPull` callback fires once"
" when the user pulls past the threshold; call `scrollviewEndRefreshing` (or "
"`lazyvstackEndRefreshing`) when your async fetch settles to dismiss the "
"spinner."
msgstr ""
"Verfügbar auf `ScrollView` und `LazyVStack`. Der `onPull`-Callback wird "
"einmal ausgelöst, wenn der Nutzer über den Schwellenwert hinaus zieht; rufen"
" Sie `scrollviewEndRefreshing` (oder `lazyvstackEndRefreshing`) auf, wenn "
"Ihr Async-Fetch abgeschlossen ist, um den Spinner zu schließen."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:413
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  ScrollView,\n"
"  scrollviewSetRefreshControl,\n"
"  scrollviewEndRefreshing,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const scroll = ScrollView();\n"
"scrollviewSetRefreshControl(scroll, async () => {\n"
"  await refreshFeed();\n"
"  scrollviewEndRefreshing(scroll);\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:427
msgid ""
"Real on iOS (`UIRefreshControl`). The macOS / Android / GTK4 / Windows "
"desktops have no native pull-to-refresh idiom — they're documented no-ops."
msgstr ""
"Echt auf iOS (`UIRefreshControl`). Die Desktops macOS / Android / GTK4 / "
"Windows haben kein natives Pull-to-Refresh-Idiom — sie sind dokumentierte "
"No-ops."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:431
msgid "Infinite scroll (`onScrollEnd`)"
msgstr "Endlos-Scroll (`onScrollEnd`)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:433
msgid ""
"Fires once when the user scrolls past `thresholdPx` (or `thresholdItems` for"
" `LazyVStack`) from the bottom; re-arms after the user scrolls back up past "
"the threshold so a single fetch is queued at a time."
msgstr ""
"Wird einmal ausgelöst, wenn der Nutzer vom unteren Rand aus über "
"`thresholdPx` (oder `thresholdItems` für `LazyVStack`) scrollt; wird neu "
"scharfgeschaltet, sobald der Nutzer wieder über den Schwellenwert nach oben "
"scrollt, sodass jeweils nur ein Fetch in der Warteschlange steht."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:437
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { ScrollView, scrollviewSetScrollEndCallback } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const scroll = ScrollView();\n"
"scrollviewSetScrollEndCallback(\n"
"  scroll,\n"
"  () => loadMore(),\n"
"  200, // threshold in pixels from the bottom\n"
");\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:448
msgid ""
"Real on every platform that has a scroll view: macOS "
"(`NSViewBoundsDidChangeNotification`), iOS "
"(`UIScrollViewDelegate.scrollViewDidScroll`), Android "
"(`View.OnScrollChangeListener`), GTK4 (`GtkAdjustment::value-changed`), "
"Windows (`WM_VSCROLL` / `WM_MOUSEWHEEL`)."
msgstr ""
"Echt auf jeder Plattform mit Scroll-View: macOS "
"(`NSViewBoundsDidChangeNotification`), iOS "
"(`UIScrollViewDelegate.scrollViewDidScroll`), Android "
"(`View.OnScrollChangeListener`), GTK4 (`GtkAdjustment::value-changed`), "
"Windows (`WM_VSCROLL` / `WM_MOUSEWHEEL`)."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:454
msgid "Platform-specific widgets"
msgstr "Plattformspezifische Widgets"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:456
msgid ""
"These exist only on specific platforms and aren't verified by the cross-"
"platform doc-tests:"
msgstr ""
"Diese existieren nur auf bestimmten Plattformen und werden nicht von den "
"plattformübergreifenden Doc-Tests verifiziert:"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:459
msgid ""
"**`Table(rows, cols, renderer)`** — macOS only. Now supports "
"`tableSetSortColumn`, `tableSetFilterText`, and multi-select since v0.5.636 "
"(#473)."
msgstr ""
"**`Table(rows, cols, renderer)`** — nur macOS. Unterstützt seit v0.5.636 "
"(#473) `tableSetSortColumn`, `tableSetFilterText` und Mehrfachauswahl."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:462
msgid "**`QRCode(data, size)`** — macOS only. Renders a QR code."
msgstr "**`QRCode(data, size)`** — nur macOS. Rendert einen QR-Code."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:463
msgid ""
"**`Canvas(width, height, draw)`** — all desktop platforms. A drawing "
"surface; see [Canvas](canvas.md)."
msgstr ""
"**`Canvas(width, height, draw)`** — alle Desktop-Plattformen. Eine "
"Zeichenfläche; siehe [Canvas](canvas.md)."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:465
msgid ""
"**`CameraView()`** — iOS only (other platforms planned). See "
"[Camera](camera.md)."
msgstr ""
"**`CameraView()`** — nur iOS (andere Plattformen geplant). Siehe "
"[Camera](camera.md)."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:468
msgid "Combobox (issue #475)"
msgstr "Combobox (Issue #475)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:470
msgid ""
"Editable text field with a filterable dropdown of suggestions. macOS uses "
"`NSComboBox` with as-you-type completion; other platforms stub the FFI today"
" (the field falls back to a plain editable field)."
msgstr ""
"Bearbeitbares Textfeld mit einem filterbaren Dropdown von Vorschlägen. macOS"
" verwendet `NSComboBox` mit Vervollständigung beim Tippen; andere "
"Plattformen stubben die FFI heute (das Feld fällt auf ein einfaches "
"bearbeitbares Feld zurück)."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:474
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { Combobox, comboboxAddItem, comboboxGetValue } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const combo = Combobox(\"\", (v) => console.log(\"picked:\", v));\n"
"comboboxAddItem(combo, \"apple\");\n"
"comboboxAddItem(combo, \"apricot\");\n"
"comboboxAddItem(combo, \"avocado\");\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:483
msgid "TreeView / Outline (issue #480)"
msgstr "TreeView / Outline (Issue #480)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:485
msgid ""
"Hierarchical disclosure list. Build the topology bottom-up via `TreeNode`"
msgstr ""
"Hierarchische Aufklapp-Liste. Bauen Sie die Topologie bottom-up über "
"`TreeNode`"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:486
msgid ""
"`treeNodeAddChild`, then mount it via `TreeView`. macOS uses "
"`NSOutlineView`; other platforms stub."
msgstr ""
"`treeNodeAddChild`, dann mounten Sie es über `TreeView`. macOS verwendet "
"`NSOutlineView`; andere Plattformen sind Stubs."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:489
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { TreeNode, treeNodeAddChild, TreeView } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const dox = TreeNode(\"docs\", \"Documents\");\n"
"treeNodeAddChild(dox, TreeNode(\"doc-1\", \"Resume.pdf\"));\n"
"treeNodeAddChild(dox, TreeNode(\"doc-2\", \"Cover Letter.pdf\"));\n"
"const root = TreeNode(\"root\", \"Files\");\n"
"treeNodeAddChild(root, dox);\n"
"const tree = TreeView(root, (id) => console.log(\"selected:\", id));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:500
msgid "Calendar (issue #481)"
msgstr "Calendar (Issue #481)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:502
msgid ""
"Month-grid date picker. macOS uses `NSDatePicker` in graphical style; other "
"platforms stub. `onChange` receives the selected date as an ISO `yyyy-MM-dd`"
" string."
msgstr ""
"Monats-Raster-Datumspicker. macOS verwendet `NSDatePicker` im grafischen "
"Stil; andere Plattformen stubben. `onChange` erhält das ausgewählte Datum "
"als ISO-`yyyy-MM-dd`-String."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:506
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { Calendar, calendarGetSelectedDate } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const cal = Calendar(2026, 5, (iso) => console.log(\"date:\", iso));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:512
msgid "DatePicker (issue #4772)"
msgstr "DatePicker (Issue #4772)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:514
msgid ""
"Compact field-style date picker — the space-saving complement to the month-"
"grid `Calendar`. Each platform uses its native compact date control: macOS "
"`NSDatePicker` (text-field-and-stepper), iOS / visionOS `UIDatePicker` "
"(`.compact`), Windows `SysDateTimePick32`, Android "
"`android.widget.DatePicker`. GTK4 has no native compact date field, so it "
"reuses `GtkCalendar`; tvOS / watchOS stub. `onChange` receives the selected "
"date as an ISO `yyyy-MM-dd` string."
msgstr ""
"Kompaktes Datumsauswahlfeld – die platzsparende Ergänzung zum Monatsraster "
"`Calendar`. Jede Plattform verwendet ihr natives kompaktes Datum-"
"Steuerelement: macOS `NSDatePicker` (Textfeld mit Schrittschaltflächen), iOS"
" / visionOS `UIDatePicker` (`.compact`), Windows `SysDateTimePick32`, "
"Android `android.widget.DatePicker`. GTK4 besitzt kein natives kompaktes "
"Datumsfeld und verwendet daher `GtkCalendar`; tvOS / watchOS sind Stubs. "
"`onChange` erhält das gewählte Datum als ISO-String `yyyy-MM-dd`."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:522
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { DatePicker, datePickerGetSelectedDate } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const picker = DatePicker(2026, 5, (iso) => console.log(\"date:\", iso));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:528
msgid "Chart (issue #474)"
msgstr "Chart (Issue #474)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:530
msgid ""
"Line / bar / pie via CoreGraphics on macOS. `kind` is `0=line`, `1=bar`, "
"`2=pie`. Apple Charts framework / SwiftUI Charts integration on iOS 16+ is a"
" follow-up."
msgstr ""
"Line- / Bar- / Pie-Diagramm via CoreGraphics auf macOS. `kind` ist `0=line`,"
" `1=bar`, `2=pie`. Apple-Charts-Framework- / SwiftUI-Charts-Integration auf "
"iOS 16+ ist ein Follow-up."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:534
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { Chart, chartAddDataPoint, chartSetTitle } from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const chart = Chart(0, 600, 400);\n"
"chartSetTitle(chart, \"Visits\");\n"
"chartAddDataPoint(chart, \"Mon\", 12);\n"
"chartAddDataPoint(chart, \"Tue\", 18);\n"
"chartAddDataPoint(chart, \"Wed\", 9);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:544
msgid "Command palette (issue #477)"
msgstr "Command-Palette (Issue #477)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:546
msgid ""
"⌘K-style fuzzy command launcher. macOS shows a floating `NSPanel`; other "
"platforms stub. Bind `commandPaletteShow()` to ⌘K via `addKeyboardShortcut` "
"to wire the default hotkey."
msgstr ""
"⌘K-artiger Fuzzy-Command-Launcher. macOS zeigt ein schwebendes `NSPanel`; "
"andere Plattformen stubben. Binden Sie `commandPaletteShow()` über "
"`addKeyboardShortcut` an ⌘K, um den Standard-Hotkey zu verdrahten."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:550
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  commandPaletteRegister,\n"
"  commandPaletteShow,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"commandPaletteRegister(\"save\", \"Save\", \"⌘S\", () => save());\n"
"commandPaletteRegister(\"export\", \"Export PDF\", \"\", () => exportPdf());\n"
"// then:\n"
"commandPaletteShow();\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:562
msgid "MapView (issue #517)"
msgstr "MapView (Issue #517)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:564
msgid ""
"Wraps `MKMapView` on macOS / iOS / visionOS / tvOS, `libshumate` on GTK4, "
"Google Maps SDK on Android (requires API key in `AndroidManifest.xml`), and "
"the SwiftUI `Map` view on watchOS. Windows remains a stub (WinUI MapControl "
"needs XAML Islands integration)."
msgstr ""
"Umhüllt `MKMapView` auf macOS / iOS / visionOS / tvOS, `libshumate` auf "
"GTK4, das Google Maps SDK auf Android (erfordert API-Key in "
"`AndroidManifest.xml`) und die SwiftUI-`Map`-View auf watchOS. Windows "
"bleibt ein Stub (WinUI MapControl benötigt XAML-Islands-Integration)."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:569
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  MapView,\n"
"  mapViewSetRegion,\n"
"  mapViewAddPin,\n"
"  mapViewSetMapType,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const map = MapView(800, 600);\n"
"mapViewSetRegion(map, 37.7749, -122.4194, 0.05, 0.05);\n"
"mapViewAddPin(map, 37.7749, -122.4194, \"San Francisco\");\n"
"mapViewSetMapType(map, 1); // 0=standard, 1=satellite, 2=hybrid\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:583
msgid "PdfView (issue #516)"
msgstr "PdfView (Issue #516)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:585
msgid ""
"`PDFView` from PDFKit on macOS / iOS / visionOS. `pdfViewLoadFile` returns 1"
" on success, 0 on failure."
msgstr ""
"`PDFView` aus PDFKit auf macOS / iOS / visionOS. `pdfViewLoadFile` gibt 1 "
"bei Erfolg, 0 bei Fehler zurück."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:588
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  PdfView,\n"
"  pdfViewLoadFile,\n"
"  pdfViewGetPageCount,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const pdf = PdfView(800, 600);\n"
"if (pdfViewLoadFile(pdf, \"/tmp/report.pdf\")) {\n"
"  console.log(\"pages:\", pdfViewGetPageCount(pdf));\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:601
msgid "RichTextEditor (issue #478)"
msgstr "RichTextEditor (Issue #478)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:603
msgid ""
"`NSTextView` with `NSAttributedString` storage on macOS. Plain-text and HTML"
" round-trip cover persistence; `richTextToggleBold` / `ToggleItalic` / "
"`ToggleUnderline` cover inline formatting via `NSResponder` actions."
msgstr ""
"`NSTextView` mit `NSAttributedString`-Speicherung auf macOS. Plain-Text- und"
" HTML-Round-Trip decken die Persistenz ab; `richTextToggleBold` / "
"`ToggleItalic` / `ToggleUnderline` decken Inline-Formatierung über "
"`NSResponder`-Aktionen ab."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:608
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import {\n"
"  RichTextEditor,\n"
"  richTextSetHtml,\n"
"  richTextGetHtml,\n"
"  richTextToggleBold,\n"
"} from \"perry/ui\";\n"
"\n"
"const editor = RichTextEditor(600, 400, (text) => console.log(text));\n"
"richTextSetHtml(editor, \"<p>Hello <b>world</b></p>\");\n"
"richTextToggleBold(editor);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/widgets.md:621
msgid "Rich tooltip (issue #479)"
msgstr "Reichhaltiger Tooltip (Issue #479)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:623
msgid ""
"`widgetSetRichTooltip(widget, content, hoverDelayMs)` — like "
"`widgetSetTooltip` but the tooltip content is itself a Perry widget. macOS "
"uses `NSPanel` + `NSTrackingArea`; other platforms stub. For plain-text "
"tooltips with VoiceOver / a11y support, prefer the simpler "
"`widgetSetTooltip`."
msgstr ""
"`widgetSetRichTooltip(widget, content, hoverDelayMs)` — wie "
"`widgetSetTooltip`, aber der Tooltip-Inhalt ist selbst ein Perry-Widget. "
"macOS verwendet `NSPanel` + `NSTrackingArea`; andere Plattformen stubben. "
"Für Plain-Text-Tooltips mit VoiceOver- / A11y-Unterstützung bevorzugen Sie "
"das einfachere `widgetSetTooltip`."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:629
msgid "WebView (issue #658)"
msgstr "WebView (Issue #658)"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:631
msgid ""
"`WebView({ url, allowedDomains?, onShouldNavigate?, ... })` embeds a real "
"browser engine — `WKWebView` on Apple, `WebView2` on Windows, `WebKitGTK "
"6.0` on Linux, `android.webkit.WebView` on Android, sandboxed `<iframe>` on "
"web. See [WebView](webview.md) for the full OAuth / callback-interception "
"pattern and the per-platform notes."
msgstr ""
"`WebView({ url, allowedDomains?, onShouldNavigate?, ... })` bettet eine "
"echte Browser-Engine ein – `WKWebView` auf Apple, `WebView2` auf Windows, "
"`WebKitGTK 6.0` auf Linux, `android.webkit.WebView` auf Android, sandboxed "
"`<iframe>` im Web. Siehe [WebView](webview.md) für das vollständige OAuth- /"
" Callback-Intercepting-Muster und die plattformspezifischen Hinweise."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:637
msgid "These are linked from their own pages where richer examples exist."
msgstr ""
"Diese werden von ihren eigenen Seiten verlinkt, wo reichhaltigere Beispiele "
"existieren."

#: src/ui/widgets.md:639
msgid "Common widget helpers"
msgstr "Allgemeine Widget-Helfer"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:641
msgid "Every widget handle accepts these:"
msgstr "Jedes Widget-Handle akzeptiert diese:"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:643
msgid "Helper"
msgstr "Helfer"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:645
msgid "`widgetSetWidth(w, n)` / `widgetSetHeight(w, n)`"
msgstr "`widgetSetWidth(w, n)` / `widgetSetHeight(w, n)`"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:645
msgid "Explicit size in points"
msgstr "Explizite Größe in Punkten"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:646
msgid "`widgetSetBackgroundColor(w, r, g, b, a)`"
msgstr "`widgetSetBackgroundColor(w, r, g, b, a)`"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:646
msgid "RGBA in \\[0, 1\\]"
msgstr "RGBA in \\[0, 1\\]"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:647
msgid "`setCornerRadius(w, r)`"
msgstr "`setCornerRadius(w, r)`"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:647
msgid "Rounded corners in points"
msgstr "Abgerundete Ecken in Punkten"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:648
msgid "`widgetSetOpacity(w, alpha)`"
msgstr "`widgetSetOpacity(w, alpha)`"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:648
msgid "Opacity in \\[0, 1\\]"
msgstr "Deckkraft in \\[0, 1\\]"

#: src/ui/widgets.md:649
