#: src/ui/state.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry uses reactive state to automatically update the UI when data changes. "
"Every snippet below is excerpted from "
"[`docs/examples/ui/state/snippets.ts`](../../examples/ui/state/snippets.ts) "
"— CI compiles and runs it on every PR."
msgstr ""
"Perry verwendet reaktiven State, um die UI automatisch zu aktualisieren, "
"wenn sich Daten ändern. Jedes untenstehende Snippet stammt aus "
"[`docs/examples/ui/state/snippets.ts`](../../examples/ui/state/snippets.ts) "
"— CI kompiliert und führt es bei jedem PR aus."

#: src/ui/state.md:8
msgid "Creating State"
msgstr "State erstellen"

#: src/ui/state.md:10
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const counter = State(0)               // number state\n"
"const username = State(\"Perry\")        // string state\n"
"const items = State<string[]>([])      // array state\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:16
msgid "`State(initialValue)` creates a reactive state container."
msgstr "`State(initialValue)` erstellt einen reaktiven State-Container."

#: src/ui/state.md:18
msgid "Reading and Writing"
msgstr "Lesen und Schreiben"

#: src/ui/state.md:20
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const value = counter.value     // Read current value\n"
"counter.set(42)                  // Set new value → triggers UI update\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:25
msgid "Every `.set()` call re-renders the widget tree with the new value."
msgstr "Jeder `.set()`-Aufruf rendert den Widget-Baum mit dem neuen Wert neu."

#: src/ui/state.md:27
msgid "Reactive Text"
msgstr "Reaktiver Text"

#: src/ui/state.md:29
msgid "Template literals with `state.value` update automatically:"
msgstr "Template-Literale mit `state.value` werden automatisch aktualisiert:"

#: src/ui/state.md:31
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const showCount = State(0)\n"
"const countLabel = Text(`Count: ${showCount.value}`)\n"
"// The text updates whenever showCount changes.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:37
msgid ""
"This works because Perry detects `state.value` reads inside template "
"literals and creates reactive bindings."
msgstr ""
"Dies funktioniert, weil Perry `state.value`-Reads innerhalb von Template-"
"Literalen erkennt und reaktive Bindings erstellt."

#: src/ui/state.md:40
msgid "Binding Inputs to State"
msgstr "Eingaben an State binden"

#: src/ui/state.md:42
msgid ""
"Input widgets expose an `onChange` callback. Forward that into a state's "
"`.set(...)` to keep the state in sync as the user types/toggles/drags:"
msgstr ""
"Input-Widgets exponieren einen `onChange`-Callback. Leiten Sie diesen in das"
" `.set(...)` eines States weiter, um den State synchron zu halten, während "
"der Nutzer tippt/umschaltet/zieht:"

#: src/ui/state.md:45
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const input = State(\"\")\n"
"const field = TextField(\"Type here...\", (v: string) => input.set(v))\n"
"\n"
"// Optional: also let input.set(\"hello\") update the field on screen.\n"
"stateBindTextfield(input, field)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:53
msgid "Input control signatures:"
msgstr "Signaturen der Eingabe-Steuerelemente:"

#: src/ui/state.md:54
msgid ""
"`TextField(placeholder, onChange)` — text input, `onChange: (value: string) "
"=> void`"
msgstr ""
"`TextField(placeholder, onChange)` — Texteingabe, `onChange: (value: string)"
" => void`"

#: src/ui/state.md:55
msgid ""
"`SecureField(placeholder, onChange)` — password input, `onChange: (value: "
"string) => void`"
msgstr ""
"`SecureField(placeholder, onChange)` — Passworteingabe, `onChange: (value: "
"string) => void`"

#: src/ui/state.md:56
msgid ""
"`Toggle(label, onChange)` — boolean toggle, `onChange: (value: boolean) => "
"void`"
msgstr ""
"`Toggle(label, onChange)` — boolescher Toggle, `onChange: (value: boolean) "
"=> void`"

#: src/ui/state.md:57
msgid ""
"`Slider(min, max, onChange)` — numeric slider, `onChange: (value: number) =>"
" void`"
msgstr ""
"`Slider(min, max, onChange)` — numerischer Slider, `onChange: (value: "
"number) => void`"

#: src/ui/state.md:58
msgid ""
"`Picker(onChange)` — dropdown, `onChange: (index: number) => void`; items "
"via `pickerAddItem`"
msgstr ""
"`Picker(onChange)` — Dropdown, `onChange: (index: number) => void`; Einträge"
" über `pickerAddItem`"

#: src/ui/state.md:60
msgid ""
"For programmatic-to-UI sync (state-drives-widget) use the dedicated binders:"
" `stateBindTextfield`, `stateBindSlider`, `stateBindToggle`, "
"`stateBindTextNumeric`, `stateBindVisibility`."
msgstr ""
"Für programmatische-zu-UI-Synchronisation (State steuert Widget) verwenden "
"Sie die dedizierten Binder: `stateBindTextfield`, `stateBindSlider`, "
"`stateBindToggle`, `stateBindTextNumeric`, `stateBindVisibility`."

#: src/ui/state.md:64
msgid "onChange Callbacks"
msgstr "onChange-Callbacks"

#: src/ui/state.md:66
msgid "Listen for state changes with the free-function `stateOnChange`:"
msgstr ""
"Hören Sie auf State-Änderungen mit der freien Funktion `stateOnChange`:"

#: src/ui/state.md:75 src/widgets/components.md:92 src/widgets/platforms.md:27
msgid "ForEach"
msgstr "ForEach"

#: src/ui/state.md:77
msgid "Render a list from numeric state (the index count):"
msgstr "Rendern Sie eine Liste aus numerischem State (die Index-Anzahl):"

#: src/ui/state.md:79
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const fruits = State([\"Apple\", \"Banana\", \"Cherry\"])\n"
"const fruitCount = State(3)\n"
"\n"
"const fruitList = VStack(16, [\n"
"    ForEach(fruitCount, (i: number) =>\n"
"        Text(`${i + 1}. ${fruits.value[i]}`),\n"
"    ),\n"
"])\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:90
msgid ""
"**Note:** `ForEach` iterates by index over a numeric state. Keep a count "
"state in sync with your array, then read the items via `array.value[i]` "
"inside the closure."
msgstr ""
"**Hinweis:** `ForEach` iteriert per Index über einen numerischen State. "
"Halten Sie einen Count-State synchron zu Ihrem Array und lesen Sie die Items"
" dann innerhalb der Closure über `array.value[i]`."

#: src/ui/state.md:94
msgid "`ForEach` re-renders the list when the count state changes:"
msgstr "`ForEach` rendert die Liste neu, wenn sich der Count-State ändert:"

#: src/ui/state.md:96
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// Add an item:\n"
"fruits.set([...fruits.value, \"Date\"])\n"
"fruitCount.set(fruitCount.value + 1)\n"
"\n"
"// Remove an item:\n"
"fruits.set(fruits.value.filter((_, i) => i !== 1))\n"
"fruitCount.set(fruitCount.value - 1)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:106
msgid "Conditional Rendering"
msgstr "Bedingtes Rendern"

#: src/ui/state.md:108
msgid "Use state to conditionally show widgets:"
msgstr "Verwenden Sie State, um Widgets bedingt anzuzeigen:"

#: src/ui/state.md:110
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const showDetails = State(false)\n"
"const detailsLabel: number = showDetails.value\n"
"    ? Text(\"Details are visible!\")\n"
"    : Spacer()\n"
"const detailsPanel = VStack(16, [\n"
"    Button(\"Toggle\", () => showDetails.set(!showDetails.value)),\n"
"    detailsLabel,\n"
"])\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:121
msgid "Multi-State Text"
msgstr "Multi-State-Text"

#: src/ui/state.md:123
msgid "Text can depend on multiple state values:"
msgstr "Text kann von mehreren State-Werten abhängen:"

#: src/ui/state.md:125
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const firstName = State(\"John\")\n"
"const lastName = State(\"Doe\")\n"
"\n"
"const greeting = Text(`Hello, ${firstName.value} ${lastName.value}!`)\n"
"// Updates when either firstName or lastName changes.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:133
msgid "State with Objects and Arrays"
msgstr "State mit Objekten und Arrays"

#: src/ui/state.md:135
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const user = State({ name: \"Perry\", age: 0 })\n"
"\n"
"// Update by replacing the whole object:\n"
"user.set({ ...user.value, age: 1 })\n"
"\n"
"const todos = State<{ text: string; done: boolean }[]>([])\n"
"\n"
"// Add a todo:\n"
"todos.set([...todos.value, { text: \"New task\", done: false }])\n"
"\n"
"// Toggle a todo (must produce a new array reference):\n"
"const next = todos.value.slice()\n"
"if (next.length > 0) {\n"
"    next[0] = { ...next[0], done: !next[0].done }\n"
"    todos.set(next)\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/ui/state.md:154
msgid ""
"**Note**: State uses identity comparison. You must create a new array/object"
" reference for changes to be detected. Mutating in-place without calling "
"`.set()` with a new reference won't trigger updates."
msgstr ""
"**Hinweis**: State verwendet Identitäts-Vergleich. Sie müssen eine neue "
"Array-/Objekt-Referenz erstellen, damit Änderungen erkannt werden. In-Place-"
"Mutationen ohne Aufruf von `.set()` mit einer neuen Referenz lösen keine "
"Updates aus."

