#: src/stdlib/fs.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry implements Node.js file system APIs for reading, writing, and managing"
" files."
msgstr ""
"Perry implementiert Node.js-Dateisystem-APIs zum Lesen, Schreiben und "
"Verwalten von Dateien."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:5
msgid "Reading Files"
msgstr "Dateien lesen"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:7
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const configPath = join(scratch, \"config.json\")\n"
"const content = readFileSync(configPath, \"utf-8\")\n"
"console.log(content)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:13
msgid "Binary File Reading"
msgstr "Binäre Datei lesen"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:15
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const imagePath = join(scratch, \"image.png\")\n"
"const buffer = readFileBuffer(imagePath)\n"
"console.log(`Read ${buffer.length} bytes`)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:21
msgid ""
"`readFileBuffer` reads files as binary data (uses `fs::read()` internally, "
"not `read_to_string()`)."
msgstr ""
"`readFileBuffer` liest Dateien als Binärdaten (verwendet intern "
"`fs::read()`, nicht `read_to_string()`)."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:23
msgid "Writing Files"
msgstr "Dateien schreiben"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:25
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const outputPath = join(scratch, \"output.txt\")\n"
"const dataPath = join(scratch, \"data.json\")\n"
"writeFileSync(outputPath, \"Hello, World!\")\n"
"writeFileSync(dataPath, JSON.stringify({ key: \"value\" }, null, 2))\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:32
msgid "File Information"
msgstr "Dateiinformationen"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:41
msgid "Directory Operations"
msgstr "Verzeichnis-Operationen"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:43
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// Create directory\n"
"const outDir = join(scratch, \"output\")\n"
"if (!existsSync(outDir)) mkdirSync(outDir)\n"
"\n"
"// Read directory contents\n"
"const files = readdirSync(scratch)\n"
"for (const file of files) {\n"
"    console.log(file)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Remove an empty directory\n"
"rmdirSync(outDir)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:58
msgid ""
"For recursive removal Perry exposes `rmRecursive` (a thin wrapper around "
"`std::fs::remove_dir_all`). Wired via "
"[\\#193](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/193) through "
"`js_fs_rm_recursive` in the LLVM backend."
msgstr ""
"Für rekursives Entfernen exponiert Perry `rmRecursive` (ein dünner Wrapper "
"um `std::fs::remove_dir_all`). Verdrahtet via "
"[\\#193](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/193) durch "
"`js_fs_rm_recursive` im LLVM-Backend."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:63
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { rmRecursive } from \"fs\";\n"
"rmRecursive(\"output\"); // Recursive remove; returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:68
msgid "Path Utilities"
msgstr "Pfad-Utilities"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:70
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const dir = dirname(configPath)\n"
"const cfgPath = join(dir, \"config.json\")\n"
"const name = basename(cfgPath)        // \"config.json\"\n"
"const abs = resolve(\"relative/path\")  // Absolute path\n"
"console.log(`${name} ${abs.length > 0}`)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:78
msgid ""
"For `import.meta.url` → filesystem path conversion, use `fileURLToPath` from"
" the `url` module:"
msgstr ""
"Für die `import.meta.url` → Dateisystempfad-Konvertierung verwenden Sie "
"`fileURLToPath` aus dem `url`-Modul:"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:81
msgid ""
"```text\n"
"import { fileURLToPath } from \"url\";\n"
"import { dirname } from \"path\";\n"
"\n"
"const dir = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:90
msgid ""
"`fs` numeric file descriptors and `fs.promises.FileHandle` objects are "
"thread-affine across `perry/thread`. Passing a numeric fd into `spawn` or "
"`parallelMap` copies only the number; the receiving thread has its own fd "
"registry, so operations fail with `EBADF`. Passing a `FileHandle` produces a"
" detached handle with `fd === -1`."
msgstr ""
"Numerische `fs`-Dateideskriptoren und `fs.promises.FileHandle`-Objekte sind "
"thread-affin über `perry/thread`. Das Übergeben eines numerischen fd an "
"`spawn` oder `parallelMap` kopiert nur die Zahl; der empfangende Thread hat "
"eine eigene fd-Registry, sodass Operationen mit `EBADF` fehlschlagen. Das "
"Übergeben eines `FileHandle` erzeugt ein abgetrenntes Handle mit `fd === "
"-1`."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:96
msgid ""
"Pass file paths across thread boundaries and reopen files inside the worker."
msgstr ""
"Übergeben Sie Dateipfade über Thread-Grenzen hinweg und öffnen Sie Dateien "
"innerhalb des Workers neu."

